About a month ago. There grew a number of small blisters on the outer side of the right palm. They are translucent. I thought it is eczema. However, I also have beriberi, and it relapses every summer. I soak my foot in Gloss Foot Potion (A traditional Chinese medicines containing Talc powder, salicylic acid, and benzoic acid), enough for a year. I also have Terafen hydrochloride cream, for my beriberi. I applied it onto my palm for a week and it showed no improvement.
Symptom:  Skin is hardening and dry, turning rough.  Have small blisters, not itchy.  Not sure if it is eczema or ring worm.  What kind of medication can heal better?  Please help.
Remark:  You can exclude the problem is caused by the use of mouse pointer.  I am left handed;
